oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Buzzards Bluff on the Cumberland river northwest of Nashville
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A black-and-white aerial-view photograph of a river bluff composed of layers of a soft, crumbling stone (possibly sandstone).
The areas above and blow the bluff are wooded, and the photo purports to show a tree with a Great Horned Owl nest with young owl present.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection
